CLI Assured = When terminating Customer's VTS Prime CLI Assured traffic, Tata Communications will endeavor to route the traffic to high call completion routes with verified CLI delivery performance only, and will use commercially reasonable endeavors to complete all roaming calls received and deliver the CLI information to the called party.
Direct Assured = When terminating Customer's VTS Prime Direct Assured traffic, Tata Communications will endeavor to route the traffic to high call completion routes only and will use commercially reasonable endeavors to complete all roaming calls received and deliver the CLI information to the called party.

All Other VTS Prime Destinations = When terminating Customer's traffic to all other VTS Prime destinations (ie: non- CLI Assured and non-Direct Assured VTS Prime Destinations), Tata Communications will route the traffic to high call completion routes only but without any kind of representation with respect to the percentage of delivery of CLI.

Comments:As in previous months BT will be applying the following surcharge for U.S. domestic carrier traffic: If in any given 30-day period more than 20% of a customer's total U.S. domestic carrier traffic does not terminate to an RBOC region, BT will apply a $0.02 per minute surcharge to all such traffic in excess of the 20%. As applicable, US RBOC codes are defined as Operating Company Numbers (OCN's) greater than or equal to 9000 as defined by the most recent Local Exchange Routing Guide (LERG). All other OCN numbers are defined as US Non-RBOC codes for purposes of rating and billing.
